verses.text_plain: Then came to Jesus scribes and Pharisees, which were of Jerusalem, saying,
verses.verse_html: 1Then came to Jesus scribes and Pharisees, which were of Jerusalem, saying,

verses.text_plain: Why do thy disciples transgress the tradition of the elders? for they wash not their hands when they eat bread.
verses.verse_html: 2Why do thy disciples transgress the tradition of the elders? for they wash not their hands when they eat bread.

verses.text_plain: But he answered and said unto them, Why do ye also transgress the commandment of God by your tradition?
verses.verse_html: 3But he answered and said unto them, Why do ye also transgress the commandment of God by your tradition?

verses.text_plain: For God commanded, saying, Honour thy father and mother: and, He that curseth father or mother, let him die the death.
verses.verse_html: 4For God commanded, saying, Honour thy father and mother: and, He that curseth father or mother, let him die the death.

verses.text_plain: But ye say, Whosoever shall say to his father or his mother, It is a gift, by whatsoever thou mightest be profited by me;
verses.verse_html: 5But ye say, Whosoever shall say to his father or his mother, It is a gift, by whatsoever thou mightest be profited by me;

verses.text_plain: And honour not his father or his mother, he shall be free. Thus have ye made the commandment of God of none effect by your tradition.
verses.verse_html: 6And honour not his father or his mother, he shall be free. Thus have ye made the commandment of God of none effect by your tradition.

verses.text_plain: Ye hypocrites, well did Esaias prophesy of you, saying,
verses.verse_html: 7Ye hypocrites, well did Esaias prophesy of you, saying,

verses.text_plain: This people draweth nigh unto me with their mouth, and honoureth me with their lips; but their heart is far from me.
verses.verse_html: 8This people draweth nigh unto me with their mouth, and honoureth me with their lips; but their heart is far from me.

verses.text_plain: But in vain they do worship me, teaching for doctrines the commandments of men.
verses.verse_html: 9But in vain they do worship me, teaching for doctrines the commandments of men.

verses.text_plain: And he called the multitude, and said unto them, Hear, and understand:
verses.verse_html: 10And he called the multitude, and said unto them, Hear, and understand:

verses.text_plain: Not that which goeth into the mouth defileth a man; but that which cometh out of the mouth, this defileth a man.
verses.verse_html: 11Not that which goeth into the mouth defileth a man; but that which cometh out of the mouth, this defileth a man.

verses.text_plain: Then came his disciples, and said unto him, Knowest thou that the Pharisees were offended, after they heard this saying?
verses.verse_html: 12Then came his disciples, and said unto him, Knowest thou that the Pharisees were offended, after they heard this saying?

verses.text_plain: But he answered and said, Every plant, which my heavenly Father hath not planted, shall be rooted up.
verses.verse_html: 13But he answered and said, Every plant, which my heavenly Father hath not planted, shall be rooted up.

verses.text_plain: Let them alone: they be blind leaders of the blind. And if the blind lead the blind, both shall fall into the ditch.
verses.verse_html: 14Let them alone: they be blind leaders of the blind. And if the blind lead the blind, both shall fall into the ditch.

verses.text_plain: Then answered Peter and said unto him, Declare unto us this parable.
verses.verse_html: 15Then answered Peter and said unto him, Declare unto us this parable.

verses.text_plain: And Jesus said, Are ye also yet without understanding?
verses.verse_html: 16And Jesus said, Are ye also yet without understanding?

verses.text_plain: Do not ye yet understand, that whatsoever entereth in at the mouth goeth into the belly, and is cast out into the draught?
verses.verse_html: 17 Do not ye yet understand, that whatsoever entereth in at the mouth goeth into the belly, and is cast out into the draught?

verses.text_plain: But those things which proceed out of the mouth come forth from the heart; and they defile the man.
verses.verse_html: 18But those things which proceed out of the mouth come forth from the heart; and they defile the man.

verses.text_plain: For out of the heart proceed evil thoughts, murders, adulteries, fornications, thefts, false witness, blasphemies:
verses.verse_html: 19For out of the heart proceed evil thoughts, murders, adulteries, fornications, thefts, false witness, blasphemies:

verses.text_plain: These are the things which defile a man: but to eat with unwashen hands defileth not a man.
verses.verse_html: 20These are the things which defile a man: but to eat with unwashen hands defileth not a man.

verses.text_plain: Then Jesus went thence, and departed into the coasts of Tyre and Sidon.
verses.verse_html: 21Then Jesus went thence, and departed into the coasts of Tyre and Sidon.

verses.text_plain: And, behold, a woman of Canaan came out of the same coasts, and cried unto him, saying, Have mercy on me, O Lord, thou Son of David; my daughter is grievously vexed with a devil.
verses.verse_html: 22And, behold, a woman of Canaan came out of the same coasts, and cried unto him, saying, Have mercy on me, O Lord, thou Son of David; my daughter is grievously vexed with a devil.

verses.text_plain: But he answered her not a word. And his disciples came and besought him, saying, Send her away; for she crieth after us.
verses.verse_html: 23But he answered her not a word. And his disciples came and besought him, saying, Send her away; for she crieth after us.

verses.text_plain: But he answered and said, I am not sent but unto the lost sheep of the house of Israel.
verses.verse_html: 24But he answered and said, I am not sent but unto the lost sheep of the house of Israel.

verses.text_plain: Then came she and worshipped him, saying, Lord, help me.
verses.verse_html: 25Then came she and worshipped him, saying, Lord, help me.

verses.text_plain: But he answered and said, It is not meet to take the children’s bread, and to cast it to dogs.
verses.verse_html: 26But he answered and said, It is not meet to take the children’s bread, and to cast it to dogs.

verses.text_plain: And she said, Truth, Lord: yet the dogs eat of the crumbs which fall from their masters’ table.
verses.verse_html: 27And she said, Truth, Lord: yet the dogs eat of the crumbs which fall from their masters’ table.

verses.text_plain: Then Jesus answered and said unto her, O woman, great is thy faith: be it unto thee even as thou wilt. And her daughter was made whole from that very hour.
verses.verse_html: 28Then Jesus answered and said unto her, O woman, great is thy faith: be it unto thee even as thou wilt. And her daughter was made whole from that very hour.

verses.text_plain: And Jesus departed from thence, and came nigh unto the sea of Galilee; and went up into a mountain, and sat down there.
verses.verse_html: 29And Jesus departed from thence, and came nigh unto the sea of Galilee; and went up into a mountain, and sat down there.

verses.text_plain: And great multitudes came unto him, having with them those that were lame, blind, dumb, maimed, and many others, and cast them down at Jesus’ feet; and he healed them:
verses.verse_html: 30And great multitudes came unto him, having with them those that were lame, blind, dumb, maimed, and many others, and cast them down at Jesus’ feet; and he healed them:

verses.text_plain: Insomuch that the multitude wondered, when they saw the dumb to speak, the maimed to be whole, the lame to walk, and the blind to see: and they glorified the God of Israel.
verses.verse_html: 31Insomuch that the multitude wondered, when they saw the dumb to speak, the maimed to be whole, the lame to walk, and the blind to see: and they glorified the God of Israel.

verses.text_plain: Then Jesus called his disciples unto him, and said, I have compassion on the multitude, because they continue with me now three days, and have nothing to eat: and I will not send them away fasting, lest they faint in the way.
verses.verse_html: 32Then Jesus called his disciples unto him, and said, I have compassion on the multitude, because they continue with me now three days, and have nothing to eat: and I will not send them away fasting, lest they faint in the way.

verses.text_plain: And his disciples say unto him, Whence should we have so much bread in the wilderness, as to fill so great a multitude?
verses.verse_html: 33And his disciples say unto him, Whence should we have so much bread in the wilderness, as to fill so great a multitude?

verses.text_plain: And Jesus saith unto them, How many loaves have ye? And they said, Seven, and a few little fishes.
verses.verse_html: 34And Jesus saith unto them, How many loaves have ye? And they said, Seven, and a few little fishes.

verses.text_plain: And he commanded the multitude to sit down on the ground.
verses.verse_html: 35And he commanded the multitude to sit down on the ground.

verses.text_plain: And he took the seven loaves and the fishes, and gave thanks, and brake them, and gave to his disciples, and the disciples to the multitude.
verses.verse_html: 36And he took the seven loaves and the fishes, and gave thanks, and brake them, and gave to his disciples, and the disciples to the multitude.

verses.text_plain: And they did all eat, and were filled: and they took up of the broken meat that was left seven baskets full.
verses.verse_html: 37And they did all eat, and were filled: and they took up of the broken meat that was left seven baskets full.

verses.text_plain: And they that did eat were four thousand men, beside women and children.
verses.verse_html: 38And they that did eat were four thousand men, beside women and children.

verses.text_plain: And he sent away the multitude, and took ship, and came into the coasts of Magdala.
verses.verse_html: 39And he sent away the multitude, and took ship, and came into the coasts of Magdala.
